In Dallas County, which has 2.6 million residents, at least 9,500 people have been tested for COVID-19, the data show.
Harris County — the state’s most populous — led with at least 12,600 residents tested.
Among the state’s largest counties, Travis County had 49 tests for every 10,000 residents, while Bexar County had only 22.
The state has been working on a county-level tally for a few weeks, said Lara Anton, a spokeswoman with the Texas Department of State Health Services.
Texas joins a growing number of states, from Louisiana to Indiana, and New York to Florida, that are reporting testing data by county.